Map:
	Map is not child interface of Collection , so it is not true collection.
	It represents data in key -value pair
	Duplicate keys not allowed
	Duplicate values allowed
	
	
	
Map  (separate hierarchy)  -->HashMap,LinkedHashMap,TreeMap,HashTable(legacy)


Common implementation classes of Map Interface:
	1. HashMap
			--> HashMap is a class  implementation of the Map interface
			--> Insertion order not maintained
			--> Duplicates key not allowed but duplicate values allowed
			--> Allows  null value
			--> Hashing technique used to store elements
			--> Value can be fetched using its key
			--> Not synchronized
			--> Heterogenious is allowed if generic is not specified  
	2. LinkedHashMap
			--> LinkedHashMap is a class  implementation of the Map interface
			--> Insertion order  maintained
			--> Duplicates key not allowed but duplicate values allowed
			--> Allows null value
			--> Hashing technique used to store elements
			--> Value can be fetched using its key
			--> Not synchronized
			--> Heterogenious is allowed if generic is not specified  
	3. TreeMap	
			--> TreeMap is a class  implementation of the Map interface
			--> Natural sorting order maintained
			--> Duplicates key not allowed but duplicate values allowed
			--> Null not allows
			--> Heterogenious is not allowed even if generic is not specified			
			